    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="693"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/868: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-03T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >February 3, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Department’s 15, February 2, 3 p.m. The Minister of Finance states that the
                    decree embodying debt plan will be signed Monday February 5th, and be published
                    in the local papers the following day.<note n="83" xml:id="d693fn83">For text of
                        decree No. 23829, February 5, 1934, see <hi rend="italic">Diario
                            Oficial</hi>, February 7, 1934, p. 2689.</note> Text of decree will be
                    telegraphed to Brazilian Embassy and may be obtained there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
